text.__SUMMARY__: Cycas curranii (Curran's pitogo) is a species of cycad endemic to the Philippines.
text.Range:
There are two subpopulations of Cycas curranii.
Mount Beaufort in the Malinao River watershed, Palawan
Bongabon and Mansalay, Mindoro Oriental provinceIn Palawan, it is also found in Puerto Princesa, and Aborlan, and Narra.
